label.value: abnormal mitotic spindle assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which assembly of the mitotic spindle is abnormal. Spindle assembly is the aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form the spindle.

label.value: abnormal regulation of cytokinesis

value.value: A regulation phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which regulation of cytokinesis is abnormal.

label.value: abnormal protein targeting via MVB pathway

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which protein targeting to the vacuole via the multivesicular sorting pathway, leading to ubiquitin-dependent protein degradation, is abnormal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal cellular response to oxidative stress

value.value: A stress response phenotype in which a cellular response to oxidative stress is abnormal.

label.value: abolished crossover

value.value: A DNA recombination phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which reciprocal DNA recombination does not occur.

label.value: abnormal cell wall organization during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cell wall organization is abnormal. Cell wall organization results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of the fungal-type cell wall.

label.value: abnormal poly(A)+ mRNA export from nucleus

value.value: A transport phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the export of polyadenylated mRNA from the nucleus is abnormal.

label.value: abnormal regulation of pseudohyphal growth

value.value: A regulation phenotype in which regulation of pseudohyphal growth is abnormal.

label.value: decreased gene conversion during vegetative growth

value.value: A DNA recombination phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which gene conversion occurs to a lower extent than normal.

label.value: abnormal cell division

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cell division is abnormal.

label.value: abnormal heterochromatin assembly by small RNA

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which assembly of heterochromatin mediated by small RNA is abnormal. Small RNA-mediated heterochromatin assembly results in transcriptional silencing.

label.value: abnormal DNA repair during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which DNA repair is abnormal.

label.value: abnormal mRNA splicing, via spliceosome

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which mRNA splicing via the spliceosome is abnormal.

label.value: abnormal actin cortical patch localization during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which actin cortical patch localization is abnormal.

label.value: abnormal regulation of establishment or maintenance of cell polarity

value.value: A regulation phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which regulation of the establishment or maintenance of cell polarity is abnormal.

label.value: abnormal cellular response to osmotic stress

value.value: A stress response phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cellular response to osmotic stress is abnormal.

definition.value: Use this term if you have assayed the response to osmotic stress at the subcellular or molecular level. If you have assayed growth of cells exposed to osmotic stress in culture, use 'sensitive to osmotic stress' (FYPO:0000270) or 'resistance to osmotic stress' (FYPO:0000851).

label.value: abnormal cellular response to hydrogen peroxide

value.value: A stress response phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cellular response to hydrogen peroxide is abnormal.

label.value: abnormal prospore formation

value.value: A sporulation phenotype in which prospore formation is abnormal. In prospore formation, each haploid nucleus becomes encapsulated by a double membrane.

label.value: abnormal horsetail movement

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which horsetail movement is abnormal. Horsetail movement is the oscillatory movement of the nucleus that takes place during meiotic prophase I.

definition.value: Consider also annotating to 'abnormal horsetail nucleus morphology' (FYPO:0002890).

label.value: abnormal establishment or maintenance of actin cytoskeleton polarity during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the establishment or maintenance of actin cytoskeleton polarity is abnormal.

label.value: increased long tract gene conversion

value.value: A DNA recombination phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of long tract gene conversion is increased.

label.value: abnormal regulation of mitotic metaphase/anaphase transition

value.value: A regulation phenotype in which regulation of the mitotic metaphase to anaphase transition is abnormal.

label.value: abnormal histone deacetylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which histone deacetylation is abnormal.

label.value: abnormal regulation of cytokinetic cell separation

value.value: A regulation phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which regulation of cytokinetic cell separation is abnormal.

label.value: abnormal ergosterol biosynthetic process

value.value: A metabolism phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which ergosterol biosynthesis is abnormal.

label.value: abnormal mRNA export from nucleus

value.value: A transport phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the export of mRNA from the nucleus is abnormal.

label.value: abnormal chromatin silencing at rDNA

value.value: A transcription regulation phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which chromatin silencing at ribosomal DNA repeats is abnormal. Chromatin silencing is the observed effect of processes that repress transcription in a region of the genome that is normally assembled into heterochromatin.

definition.value: Chromatin silencing phenotypes may reflect the assembly or maintenance of heterochromatin. See the GO cellular component term 'heterochromatin' (GO:0000792), and the biological process term 'heterochromatin organization' (GO:0070828).

label.value: abnormal cellular response to caffeine

value.value: A cellular response phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the cellular response to caffeine is abnormal.

label.value: abnormal cellular response to cadmium ion

value.value: A cellular response phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the cellular response to cadmium ions is abnormal.

label.value: abnormal attachment of spindle microtubules to kinetochore during meiosis I

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the attachment of spindle microtubules to the kinetochore during the first meiotic nuclear division is abnormal.

definition.value: Abnormal kinetochore attachment may cause separation of sister chromatids during the first meiotic nuclear division, leading to equational segregation. If this occurs, also annotate to 'equational sister chromatid separation during meiosis I' (FYPO:0005634).

label.value: abnormal cellular response to heat

value.value: A cellular response phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the cellular response to heat is abnormal.

definition.value: Use this term if you have assayed the response to heat at the subcellular or molecular level. If you have assayed growth of cells exposed to heat in culture, use 'sensitive to heat' (FYPO:0000082) or 'resistance to heat' (FYPO:0002626).

label.value: abnormal vesicle-mediated transport during vegetative growth

value.value: A transport phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which vesicle-mediated transport is abnormal.

definition.value: This term can be used for protein transport or for the movement of other substances (e.g. lipids or ions) via vesicles. If it is used for a protein transport phenotype, we recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay.

label.value: abnormal mitotic chromosome condensation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which mitotic chromosome condensation is abnormal.

label.value: abnormal intracellular protein transport during vegetative growth

value.value: A transport phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which intracellular protein transport is abnormal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal negative regulation of mitotic DNA replication initiation

value.value: A regulation phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which negative regulation of the initiation of mitotic DNA replication is abnormal. May result in re-replication of all or part of the genome.

label.value: abnormal DNA replication

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which DNA replication is abnormal.

label.value: decreased Mre11 complex assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of Mre11 complex assembly is decreased.

label.value: increased protein oxidation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of oxidation of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, is increased, resulting in the accumulation of proteins with oxidative modifications including carbonylated proteins.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased centromeric outer repeat transcript level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which RNAs transcribed from the centromere outer repeat region are present at greater levels than normal.

definition.value: This term encompasses both unprocessed RNA transcribed from the centromere outer repeat region and siRNAs derived by dicer-mediated processing of the primary transcripts. Use this term only for levels of RNA transcribed from endogenous centromere outer repeat sequences. For levels of RNA transcribed from an exogenous reporter gene placed in the outer repeat region, consider 'decreased chromatin silencing at centromere outer repeat region' (FYPO:0003412).

label.value: elongated multiseptate vegetative cell

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell is longer, and has a greater length:diameter ratio, than normal, and has more than one septum.

label.value: lemon-shaped cell

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a single cell grows in the form of a lemon. A lemon shape is defined mathematically as having a quadric surface in three dimensions obtained by rotating less than half of a circular arc about an axis passing through the endpoints of the arc.

label.value: snowman-shaped spore

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a spore assumes a snowman shape, having two connected parts, roughly spherical, of different sizes.

label.value: chromosome loss during mitotic chromosome segregation

value.value: A chromosome segregation phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which one or more chromosome or minichromosome is not correctly segregated to either daughter cells during mitosis.

label.value: lagging mitotic chromosomes

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which sister chromatids do not move towards the spindle poles at the same time during mitosis, but instead one or more chromosomes remain distant from the spindle pole after the bulk of the DNA has separated. Mitotic sister chromatid segregation may stop before completing separation of chromosomes, or may eventually be completed.

definition.value: Chromosome lagging may reflect a delay in detachment of sister chromatids from each other ('chromatid separation' as defined by GO:0051306), polewards movement (GO:0007079), or both. Consider also annotating to 'unequal mitotic sister chromatid segregation' (FYPO:0003241) or one of its descendants, because chromosomes that lag at anaphase are often missegregated at telophase.

label.value: cut

value.value: An inviable phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell undergoes septation despite abnormal mitotic nuclear division, such that the septum physically divides the nucleus into two parts, giving rise to inviable daughter cells.

label.value: abnormal actomyosin contractile ring actin filament organization

value.value: A cytokinesis phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the assembly and distribution of actin filaments and associated proteins does not occur normally, resulting in the formation of an abnormal actomyosin contractile ring in which actin is absent or mislocalized.

label.value: abnormal actomyosin contractile ring myosin filament organization

value.value: A cytokinesis phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which myosin filaments are not localized normally within the actomyosin contractile ring.

label.value: split actomyosin contractile ring

value.value: A cytokinesis phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the actomyosin contractile ring splits upon initiation of contraction during anaphase B, resulting in the formation of a primary ring that undergoes constriction and a secondary ring that does not constrict.

label.value: long cytoplasmic microtubules

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells form cytoplasmic microtubules that are longer than normal.

label.value: abnormal cytoplasmic interphase microtubule nucleation

value.value: A microtubule cytoskeleton organization phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which nucleation of cytoplasmic microtubules is abnormal during interphase of the mitotic cell cycle. Normally, microtubules are nucleated from interphase microtubule organizing centers (iMTOCs) and from the cytoplasmic face of the spindle pole body (SPB).
